Title: Second Order Formalism for Fermions
Authors: J. L. Cort\'es, J. Gamboa and L. Vel\'azquez
Comments: 13 pp, Plain TeX, IPNO-TH 92/82, DFTUZ 92/13
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B313 (1993) 108-114
\\
  A new formulation of fermions based on a second order action is proposed. An
analysis of the $U(1)$ anomaly allows us to test the validity of the formalism
at the quantum level. This formulation gives a new perpective to the
introduction of parity non-invariant interactions.
